          "date": "2013-03-19 20:30:52.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-2948 osc: Add timeout to osc_lru_reserve",
        "message": "LU-2948 osc: Add timeout to osc_lru_reserve\n\nIf a thread ends up sleeping on the osc_lru_waitq, this patch ensures it\nis woken up at least every 60 seconds and tries to perform LRU\nreclaiming again. When the time out hits, a message is printed to the\nconsole stating this happened. In addition, a lustre debug log is dumped\nwith D_CACHE information to help debug why the thread failed to reclaim\nin the first place and why it was never woken up.\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nSigned-off-by: Prakash Surya <surya1@llnl.gov>\nChange-Id: Iac643f2abb424f523d32265f93b4d05c828b0649\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
